single level in the hierarchy is also called a "region".
hierarchy levels often have fewer nodes and therefore less spatial resolvability.
hierarchy levels can reuse patterns learned at the lower levels by combining them to memorize more complex patterns.
learning and inference modes, sensory data comes into the bottom level nodes.
generation mode, the bottom level nodes output the generated pattern of a given category.
