training, a node receives a temporal sequence of spatial patterns as its input.
inference (recognition), the node calculates the set of probabilities that a pattern belongs to each known coincidence.
it calculates the probabilities that the input represents each temporal group.
set of probabilities assigned to the groups is called a node's "belief" about the input pattern.
